rsWSDApplicationServersTable.name: rsWSDApplicationServersTable
rsWSDApplicationServersTable.description: Table containing the list of application servers to which the clients requested are dispatched.

rsWSDApplicationServerEntry.name: rsWSDApplicationServerEntry
rsWSDApplicationServerEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDServerName.name: rsWSDServerName
rsWSDServerName.description: The name assigned by the user to the server.

rsWSDServerOperStatus.name: rsWSDServerOperStatus
rsWSDServerOperStatus.description: Operational status of application on server. active - server is active notInService - server is or will become inactive. Existing sessions will be redirected to other servers. noNewSessions - server will receive no new sessions. Existing sessions are allowed to complete.

rsWSDServerWeight.name: rsWSDServerWeight
rsWSDServerWeight.description: A numerical weight assigned by the user in order to impose some priority mechanism on the server dispatchers considerations of which server to choose for attaching a client .

rsWSDServerAttachedUsersNumber.name: rsWSDServerAttachedUsersNumber
rsWSDServerAttachedUsersNumber.description: Number of currently active users attached to this server.

rsWSDServerPeakLoad.name: rsWSDServerPeakLoad
rsWSDServerPeakLoad.description: Maximal number of frames per second dispatched to server since last reset.

rsWSDServerFramesRate.name: rsWSDServerFramesRate
rsWSDServerFramesRate.description: Number of frames per second dispatched to server.

rsWSDServerFramesLoad.name: rsWSDServerFramesLoad
rsWSDServerFramesLoad.description: Number of frames per second dispatched to server.

rsWSDServerStatus.name: rsWSDServerStatus
rsWSDServerStatus.description: Administative status of appliaction on server.

rsWSDServerOperMode.name: rsWSDServerOperMode
rsWSDServerOperMode.description: This variable indicate the status of the server, the WSD will not send any messages to a backup server unless all other server are down status. In case of more then one backup server, the WSD will decide to which backup server to send the massages acordinf to rsWSDWeight.

rsWSDMultiplexedServerPort.name: rsWSDMultiplexedServerPort
rsWSDMultiplexedServerPort.description: The port on which this server listens to the multiplexed port of its farm. Port 0 - no multiplexing on this server

rsWSDServerType.name: rsWSDServerType
rsWSDServerType.description: This variable indicates the server's type. Regular type servers have no other connection to the network except this WSD. Distributed type servers are remote WSDs. A remote type server is a server cpnnected to the network at a different entry point.

rsWSDServerConnectionLimit.name: rsWSDServerConnectionLimit
rsWSDServerConnectionLimit.description: The maximal number of client sessions which can be opened on this sever.

rsWSDServerAdminStatus.name: rsWSDServerAdminStatus
rsWSDServerAdminStatus.description: Administrative status of application on server. enable - activates the server. The rsWSDServerOperStatus will change to active. disable - stops the server. The rsWSDServerOperStatus will change to notInService. shutdown - gracefully shuts down the server. The rsWSDServerOperStatus will change to noNewSessions.

rsWSDServerRedirectTo.name: rsWSDServerRedirectTo
rsWSDServerRedirectTo.description: String to be used by HTTP redirection.

rsWSDServerClientNATStatus.name: rsWSDServerClientNATStatus
rsWSDServerClientNATStatus.description: enable or disable the NAT client feature for this server Default value is disable

rsWSDFarmTable.name: rsWSDFarmTable
rsWSDFarmTable.description: In this table the WSD version 2 saves the general parameters per server farme IP Addr.

rsWSDFarmEntry.name: rsWSDFarmEntry
rsWSDFarmEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDFarmAddress.name: rsWSDFarmAddress
rsWSDFarmAddress.description: The IP Address of the WEB farm.

rsWSDFarmName.name: rsWSDFarmName
rsWSDFarmName.description: The name assigned by the user to this WEB farm.

rsWSDClientsLifeTime.name: rsWSDClientsLifeTime
rsWSDClientsLifeTime.description: Maximal period of time in seconds a non-active client is kept in the clients table.

rsWSDCheckConnectivityMethod.name: rsWSDCheckConnectivityMethod
rsWSDCheckConnectivityMethod.description: Application port for TCP or UDP connectivity check.

rsWSDCheckConnectivityInterval.name: rsWSDCheckConnectivityInterval
rsWSDCheckConnectivityInterval.description: Polling interval in seconds for servers polling.

rsWSDCheckConnectivityRetries.name: rsWSDCheckConnectivityRetries
rsWSDCheckConnectivityRetries.description: This variable indicate the Minimal number of unsuccessful polling attempts before considering a server disconnected.

rsWSDClientsConnectDenials.name: rsWSDClientsConnectDenials
rsWSDClientsConnectDenials.description: This variable indicate the Number of connection requests from clients that were denied by the the server dispatcher.

rsWSDFarmStatus.name: rsWSDFarmStatus
rsWSDFarmStatus.description: This variable indicate the Administative status of this entry. Use for delete an entry in this table.

rsWSDMultiplexedFarmPort.name: rsWSDMultiplexedFarmPort
rsWSDMultiplexedFarmPort.description: The port on this farm's virtual IP for which port multiplexing is enabled. Port 0 - multiplexing is disabled

rsWSDFarmDistThreshold.name: rsWSDFarmDistThreshold
rsWSDFarmDistThreshold.description: This variable indicates the treshold above which the WSD starts distributing traffic to distributed WSDs. The significance of this parameter varies according to the load balancing algorithm chosen.

rsWSDFarmTrafficThreshold.name: rsWSDFarmTrafficThreshold
rsWSDFarmTrafficThreshold.description: This variable indicates the treshold above which the WSD signals to all the distributed WSDs not to send traffic to it.

rsWSDFarmRedirectionMode.name: rsWSDFarmRedirectionMode
rsWSDFarmRedirectionMode.description: This variable indicates if redirection is enabled and if enable which redirection mode is established (http, triangle or dns redirection). If redirection is disabled (i.e. -noRedirection), HTTP traffic is handled as all other traffic.

rsNsdFarmRegister.name: rsNsdFarmRegister
rsNsdFarmRegister.description: Enable/Disable farm's registration in the WINS server.

rsWSDFarmMode.name: rsWSDFarmMode
rsWSDFarmMode.description: This variable indicate the mode of this farm weather its my farm or farm of my main WSD which this WSD make redundancy

rsWSDExtendedConnectivityCheckInterval.name: rsWSDExtendedConnectivityCheckInterval
rsWSDExtendedConnectivityCheckInterval.description: The frequency at which an extended http check will be sent if rsWSDCheckConnectivityMethod is equal to 2. After this number of normal http checks a extended http check will be performed.

rsWSDConnectivityCheckUrl.name: rsWSDConnectivityCheckUrl
rsWSDConnectivityCheckUrl.description: The absolute path of the web page to be requested in the extended connectivity check. Example: ~smith/home.html

rsWSDFarmClientMode.name: rsWSDFarmClientMode
rsWSDFarmClientMode.description: Client mode for this farm. How a single client's sessions are handled in the client table. Regular: all sessions to the same server, differentiated by destination port. EntryPerSession: all sessions to the same server, differentiated by both ports. ServerPerSession: new server selected for every session. RemoveEntry: extends EntryPerSession by removing terminated TCP sessions. RemoveServerPerSession: extends ServerPerSession to remove terminated TCP sessions.

rsWSDDNSRedir2ndMode.name: rsWSDDNSRedir2ndMode
rsWSDDNSRedir2ndMode.description: Secondary choice to be used with DNS redirection, in case that a client tries to connect to the virtual IP although it can not receive local service.

rsWSDFarmHttpRedirectionMode.name: rsWSDFarmHttpRedirectionMode
rsWSDFarmHttpRedirectionMode.description: Http redirection mode : IP address redirection mode or URL address redirection mode.

rsWSDFarmOperStatus.name: rsWSDFarmOperStatus
rsWSDFarmOperStatus.description: Farm status. Active - farm is active. NotInService - service is not available.

rsWSDFarmCookieKey.name: rsWSDFarmCookieKey
rsWSDFarmCookieKey.description: String representing the cookie key to look for. A value also indicates that the farm does cookie-based load balancing.

rsWSDConnCheckUserName.name: rsWSDConnCheckUserName
rsWSDConnCheckUserName.description: Username used for extended connectivity checks.

rsWSDConnCheckPassword.name: rsWSDConnCheckPassword
rsWSDConnCheckPassword.description: Password used for extended connectivity checks.

rsWSDClientsTable.name: rsWSDClientsTable
rsWSDClientsTable.description: Table containing the list of clients currently attached to a server.

rsWSDClientEntry.name: rsWSDClientEntry
rsWSDClientEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDFarmAddr.name: rsWSDFarmAddr
rsWSDFarmAddr.description: IP Address of the WEB farm the client trough which the client connected.

rsWSDAttachedServerAddr.name: rsWSDAttachedServerAddr
rsWSDAttachedServerAddr.description: IP Address of server currently serving this client.

rsWSDClientLastActivityTime.name: rsWSDClientLastActivityTime
rsWSDClientLastActivityTime.description: Indicates when the last frame from the client was dispatched. Measured in seconds since device re-initialization.

rsWSDClientAttachmentTime.name: rsWSDClientAttachmentTime
rsWSDClientAttachmentTime.description: Indicates when the client was attached. Measured in seconds since device re-initialization.

rsWSDClientType.name: rsWSDClientType
rsWSDClientType.description: This variable indicates the administrative type of this entry.

rsWSDClientStatus.name: rsWSDClientStatus
rsWSDClientStatus.description: This variable indicates the administrative status of this entry. Used to delete an entry of this table.

rsWSDLoadReportEntry.name: rsWSDLoadReportEntry
rsWSDLoadReportEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDReportDstFarmAddress.name: rsWSDReportDstFarmAddress
rsWSDReportDstFarmAddress.description: The farm IP address in the remote system which corresponding rsWSDReportFarmAddress.

rsWSDReportLclSuperFarmAddr.name: rsWSDReportLclSuperFarmAddr
rsWSDReportLclSuperFarmAddr.description: The Superfarm IP address in the local system

rsWSDReportDstIpAddress.name: rsWSDReportDstIpAddress
rsWSDReportDstIpAddress.description: The IP address of the remote system which should receive the load report.

rsWSDReportMapFarmAddress.name: rsWSDReportMapFarmAddress
rsWSDReportMapFarmAddress.description: The virtual address to which the request should be mapped when a distributed unit redirects traffic using the triangulation method.

rsWSDReportRdnDstIpAddr.name: rsWSDReportRdnDstIpAddr
rsWSDReportRdnDstIpAddr.description: The IP address of the redundant remote system which should receive the load report.

rsWSDReportDstSuperFarmAddr.name: rsWSDReportDstSuperFarmAddr
rsWSDReportDstSuperFarmAddr.description: The Superfarm IP address in the remote system

rsWSDFarmMappingEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDMappingAddress.description: The sub-virtual address of the farm. A distributed WSD directs the clients to this address.

rsWSDMappingFarmAddress.description: The local virtual address of the farm. A couple of sub virtual addresses can belong to the same farm address. The local servers are defined per farm address.

rsWSDOriginalAddress.name: rsWSDOriginalAddress
rsWSDOriginalAddress.description: The original IP address. This address replaces the server IP address when responding to the client. This IP address is the virtual IP address which the customer approached.

rsWSDMappingAdminStatus.name: rsWSDMappingAdminStatus
rsWSDMappingAdminStatus.description: Indicates/controls the sub virtual address mapping enabling.

rsWSDLoadReportInterval.name: rsWSDLoadReportInterval
rsWSDLoadReportInterval.description: The interval in seconds between two load reports.

rsWSDLoadReportTimeout.name: rsWSDLoadReportTimeout
rsWSDLoadReportTimeout.description: The timeout in seconds between two load report messages.

rsWSDPortFarmTable.name: rsWSDPortFarmTable
rsWSDPortFarmTable.description: A table for managing the farm decision according to the incoming port.

rsWSDPortFarmEntry.name: rsWSDPortFarmEntry
rsWSDPortFarmEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDPortMainAddress.name: rsWSDPortMainAddress
rsWSDPortMainAddress.description: The Main IP address given by clients.

rsWSDPortFarmAddress.description: The IP Address to use for the port.

rsWSDPortFarmHeader.name: rsWSDPortFarmHeader
rsWSDPortFarmHeader.description: HTTP Header field for token parsing.

rsWSDStaticProximityFarmAddress.description: The IP Address of the WEB farm.
